Cell.Text: Ask Esbern. If he doesn't know himself, he'll know where to find it out.
[S] <<Shared>> Try the mages of the College of Winterhold. They have a deep interest in such arcana.
[S] Such blasphemies are the calling of mages, not followers of the Way. | Take your question to the College of Winterhold. They may be able to help you.

Node.Caption: MQ205ElderScrollTopic: Any idea where to find the Elder Scroll?

Cell.Text: Were the Greybeards any help? Did they know this anything about the Shout used against Alduin?
[S] An Elder Scroll? That's not going to be easy to come by. | Esbern's your man for that kind of thing. He may be able to at least point you in the right direction.

Node.Caption: MQ205DelphineIntroA1: No, but I know how to find out. I need an Elder Scroll.

Cell.Text: Paarthurnax. The dragon, that the Greybeards have been protecting for all these years.
You've discovered... what?
He's a dragon. Not just any dragon, but the right hand of Alduin, responsible for many atrocities during the ancient Dragon War.
[S] He needs to die. He deserves to die. And it falls to you to kill him. | Until he's dead... well, I'm sorry, but we would dishonor our oaths as Blades if we continued to help you.

[S] The Blades have been hunting him for centuries, but he was protected by the Greybeards and then the Emperors. | Justice demands that he die for his crimes. Until he is dead, I'm afraid my oath as a Blade prevents me from offering you aid and comfort.

That's fine. We needed his help. Now we don't, and it's long past time for him to pay for his crimes. | And he's not just any dragon. He was the right hand of Alduin. | He committed atrocities so infamous they are still remembered, thousands of years later.

All well and good. But did you know that he was Alduin's chief lieutenant in ancient times? Responsible for terrible atrocities? | It's true that his crimes are long in the past, but justice does not count the passage of years.

Node.Caption: MQPaarthurnaxIntroA2: Turns out he's a dragon. But he helped me.

Cell.Text: There's one more thing. We know about Paarthurnax.
I'm afraid there's a further problem. A serious one. I've discovered who the Greybeards' leader really is.
I'm afraid there's a problem. A serious one. I've discovered who the Greybeards' leader really is.
Ah, you're back. I hope you've made some progress on tracking down this Shout we need to defeat Alduin?

[S] Ah, indeed? There's a pretty puzzle. Not the kind of thing you'll find in your local bookshop. Let me think... | Perhaps the College of Winterhold. What learning there is in Skyrim is gathered there. | One of the mages there may be able to put you on the trail of this Elder Scroll.
I'll need an Elder Scroll to get any further. I'm working on locating it.
[S] Well... a pretty puzzle indeed. Not the kind of thing you'll find in your local bookshop. I'm sure you're up to the task, though.

Node.Caption: MQ205EsbernIntroA1: I'll need an Elder Scroll to get any further.

Cell.Text: So... you spoke to Paarthurnax. The dragonblood burns bright within you. | Did he tell you what you wanted to know? Did he teach you the Dragonrend Shout?
[S] So be it. If he believes it is necessary for you to learn this... we will bow to his wisdom.

Node.Caption: MQ205ArngeirIntroA1: No, but he told me how to find out.

Cell.Text: [S] We have never concerned ourselves with the Scrolls. The gods themselves would rightly fear to tamper with such things. | As for where to find it... such blasphemies have always been the stock in trade of the mages of Winterhold. | They may be able to tell you something about the Elder Scroll you seek.

Node.Caption: MQ205ArngeirIntroB1: I need the Elder Scroll the ancients used. Do you know where to find it?

Cell.Text: Fascinating! So the ancients were more daring... or foolhardy... similar to the Dragon Break itself, although less far-reaching... | This Elder Scroll might be able to show you the past in some way, then... yes, yes, it could work.

Node.Caption: MQ205EsbernIntroB1: Turns out the ancient Nords used it to send Alduin forward through time.

Cell.Text: Paarthurnax? That name is familiar... the legendary leader of the Greybeards? | I would not have expected a scholar of such an esoteric turn of mind among their ranks.

Node.Caption: MQ205EsbernIntroB2: I don't really know. Paarthurnax told me it would work.

Cell.Text: Hmm. Well, if that's what the Greybeards told you, I confess I don't have a better plan. | So little is known about the Elder Scrolls, almost anything is possible where they're concerned. Artifacts of truly inconceivable power.

Node.Caption: MQ205EsbernIntroB3: I can use it to learn Dragonrend from the ancient Nords who defeated Alduin.
